description: LibriVox recording of Blackthorn Farm, by Arthur Applin. Read by Tony Oliva. But he was afraid. He had failed twice already. He could not afford to fail a third time. He had no idea how deeply Rupert was in debt. Rupert himself had only just realised it. And in desperation he had gambled to save himself.
